thread.title_full: UW homecoming 1965: Beavers give Huskies a scare | The Seattle Times

author: Colin Diltz
title: UW homecoming 1965: Beavers give Huskies a scare
text:
Fifty years ago, Washington faced off with Oregon State during the homecoming football game.
The Seattle Times’ Walt Parietti summarized the action: “Homecoming fans got their money’s worth yesterday. They sat spellbound for 59 minutes of excitement, punctuated by 15 minutes of horror.”
The horror was the second quarter: Oregon State scored 21 points.
But when UW’s Ralph Winters intercepted a pass at the goal line in the last minute of the game, the Huskies were victorious, 28-21.
See more historical photos 
Winters earned the game ball and said he planned to put it on the mantle of his crew house.
The Nov. 14, 1965, Times headline was “Winters Chills Beavers with Late Interception.” Four staff photographers were assigned to cover the game: Vic Condiotty, Josef Scaylea, Larry Dion and Robert I. Peterson.
The team would end the season with five wins, five losses. The class of 1965 is planning a reunion at UW during this year’s homecoming . On Saturday, the Huskies will face the Oregon Ducks.
 
Colin Diltz
